President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Daniel L. Shields III is nominated for Ambassador to Brunei Darussalam at the Department of State. Joseph M. Torsella is nominated for United States Representative to the United Nations for U.N. Management and Reform. Andrew Traver is nominated for Director of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms, and Explosives at the Department of Justice. Additionally, Barbaralee Diamonstein-Spielvogel is appointed as a Member of the American Battle Monuments Commission. These individuals are expected to serve the American people in their new roles.